<h2>Types of approvals</h2>
<p>Authorisations may be issued for operations near people, in complex environments, beyond visual line of sight, or for essential services requiring specific mitigations.</p>
<h2>Assessment principles</h2>
<p>Applications are assessed on hazard identification, risk controls, pilot competence, aircraft suitability and organisational capability to maintain safe operations.</p>
<h2>Documents usually required</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Operational risk assessment and concept of operations.</li>
  <li>Pilot competency evidence.</li>
  <li>Maintenance and technical assurance records.</li>
  <li>Emergency and contingency procedures.</li>
</ul>
<div class="callout"><strong>Future portal:</strong> A dedicated application tracker will be introduced to submit documents and monitor assessment progress.</div>
